<TITLE> BCB extends Faruque-Athar contracts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 30 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) Monday extended the contracts of two selectors Faruque Ahmed and Athar Ali for one month, said a BCB press release. The contractual tenures of chief Faruque Ahmed and member Athar Ali were to expire on Tuesday (July 31), but their contracts have been extended for one month till August 31,2007. "The selectors have agreed to the arrangement in the greater interest of cricket and in view of the deadlines for selection of the national squad for the ICC World Twenty20 and the national academy squad for the Tour of Australia," read the BCB statement. The national squad for the Twenty20 World Cup has to be declared by August 11. "Twenty20 World Cup and the academy squad tour of Australia are very important assignments and we have agreed to the BCB proposal in the greater interest of cricket," Faruque told bdnews24.com Monday. Meanwhile, the BCB has a two-year contract with Akram Khan, the other member of three-member selection committee. 
